Trashy versus resourceful.

Reusing old things doesn’t have to be considered trashy. But leaving garbage lying around everywhere IS trashy! The wind will take it to the neighbors. It will get caught in fences and be eaten by wildlife. It will become part of your topsoil and NEVER decompose.
So pick it up!

Garbage is a huge issue for me. I would love to produce no waste, and we TRY, but when we have to use plastic, or any other material that can’t be recycled or repurposed (compost and animal scraps count!), we make sure it gets picked up. Moving to a new farm means that I am constantly also picking up other pieces garbage ☹️

What is the last piece of garbage you picked up?

#reducereuserecycle #nowaste #nosingleuseplastic #uselessplastic #michiganhomesteading #michiganhomestead #firstgenerationfarmers #smallhomestead #chickenfarmer #delawarechicken

Yes I could have bought strawberries already picked and clean, and blemish free. But we are making memories!
And strawberry cake and smoothies, say the kids.

We’re out! Winifred and William are 14 months now and we just ran out of @earthmamaorganics Diaper Balm.
This has been a favorite for me with all six of my kids. 

We don’t just use it on bums around here. Scrapes, cuts, imaginary ouchies, chaffing, unexplained redness, chapped lips, bums of course, and more. 

I’m the weirdo offering friends my diaper balm from my bag like I’m Mary Poppins and can cure what ails them 🤪

Anywho, I’ll be jumping on to order more, and I might throw in another tinted sunscreen for myself.
And a chapstick.
And belly oil (for my face)

Happy shopping!

Last Island post before the big reveal!!
We snagged this old bowling alley lane a few months ago and it’s just been patiently waiting to be turned into our island. I’m so proud of the hard work Brian has put into cutting the lumber for the base! It’s everything we dreamed of, come true! My hands are still numb from sanding, but I’m starting finishing touches tonight.

It should be done this weekend and in the kitchen.

Any guesses on what color the base will be?

It’s in! 
It’s beautiful.
And it will never be this clean again 🤪

#largefamilies #familymeals #dinnerprep #homerenovation #cookfromscratch #growyourownfood
We did a thing! I know summer is ending, and I wish we did it sooner. Thankfully, we have a pretty large concrete basement 🫣

One of my favorite sights, goats INSIDE their pasture!

One section of fence was missing and we quickly ran hot wire this past spring. Well fast forward to many rains and the grass was so high we had to turn the fence off. So the goats have been vacationing all over the property! 

Yesterday the girls helped cut down all the grass and weeds, and today Brian and I put in posts, stretched fence, and re attached the hot wire. And BAM!! Secure goats again. 

Good fences make good neighbors 💯😄

Today has already been so full!

On the full moon, Josephine and I filled a jar with water and set it outside in the moonlight. We spoke our good intensions and hopes to it for the next moon cycle, and we left it until morning.

The next day, my jar was filled with bubbles. I drank the whole thing that next 24 hours each sip whispering inside my head my emotional goals and desired growth.

THat was yesterday.
Today we stopped at a garage sale. 
Made a new friend.
Found a good deal on a hope chest.
Bartered our labor of cleaning up his apple trees of fallen fruit, in trade for all the fruit collected. 
Been invited back to fish his stocked spring fed pond to feed in ur family.
Been invited back to clean up more apples when we are ready.

🌟 The girls were rewarded for their hard work, and I might even make it BACK outside to start the next pasture fence (which if you have animals-you know is never ending. 🐐

Yesterday was the big pig escape.
Brian wasn’t home. Thankfully I’ve spent extra time with them lately, so they didn’t give us TOO MUCH trouble. 

It was their way of telling us they wanted in the new chicken run to help cut the grass.

Today they are very happy chomping grass. I even left the hose on for an extended period of time so they could help dig the chickens a watering hole.

I’m planning to have the next barn pasture done in a week and I will move them to there next to do the same thing. Then off to the garden!

Finally the girls are paying us back!

Josephine wants to focus on photography this year. And I would LOVE to encourage this! Dusting off my old Nikon 😎

It’s amazing how quickly they change. Just when you get used to something, it changes. 

Winnie has found her inner diva and has started throwing fits! Last night actually hanging from the refrigerator handle and screaming.

William is cutting 147 teeth and has been clingy and very much a snuggler the last few weeks, but still the happiest of ALL of my babies. Can’t you tell 😃

*Side note, Walmart now carries organic cotton clothes! I have no idea when that happened.

New Autumn traditions.
We are joyful and exhausted.

I am so bad at receiving things. Gifts, words of affirmation, acts of service, and physical touch lately if I’m being honest.

I took six kids to Great Wolf Lodge this week, and another couple bought me a beer after they realized I was solo parenting.

I should have savored that. Thanked them genuinely and thought about myself in a positive way. But I couldn’t. 
I don’t feel I am ever enough. Don’t let this photo, or any others fool you. 

I’m not asking for encouragement, or reassurance. I want to be transparent. This life is hard. Parenting kids, ANY amount, is HARD! Even if I post fun photos, you see us doing fun things, it doesn’t mean I’m a badass at this parenting thing.

I’m working at recording my affirmations. Speaking my positive intentions and getting back to my gentle parenting.

Be real with me for a minute. Fill in this positive affirmation for yourself.
I am…

*mine in the comments*

We had THE MOST FUN TODAY.
I’ve started living my best life here in Michigan. 

I took a few weeks off to mourn the end our family style parenting with both myself and Brian home. It may have gotten a little depressing and dark. And I haven’t given credit where it’s due to my husband. I haven’t shared our joys and accomplishments because I’ve been having a passive pity party.
I’m done now 😜

Today me and the 6 kids attempted a corn maze… Can you imagine? What could go wrong!?

We got so lost. Thank goodness the 4 big kids loved it 🤪

Moved the herd to the winter barn. Heated water, hay, and a new field of grass to munch before the snow comes.
